OCG: WHEEL - Lord Impulse

Tyler10nyson (041523) 16/07/2024
0 86
Update information about new cards - OCG

[ROTA] New "Dominus" trap revealed in RAGE OF THE ABYSS ! ✨

P/s: Sorry for the slow upload, lol, lately I need to rest...



Lord Impulse


Normal Trap Card

If your opponent controls a card, you can activate this card from your hand. When a card or effect is activated that includes an effect that Special Summons a monster(s): Negate that effect, then if you have a Trap in your GY, destroy that card. If you activated this card from your hand, you cannot activate the effects of LIGHT, EARTH, and WIND monsters for the rest of this Duel. You can only activate 1 "Dominus Impulse" per turn.

Source: Yugioh JP
Translated by YGOrganization

Instructions for Playing Snake-Eye Fire King

These snake-eye fire kings have very strong combo abilities, great recovery or backup next turn


Fire King and Snake-Eye are both FIRE, the Original card is searched because Snake-Eye's chubby Poplar can jump another equally chubby Ponix , the good thing here is that Poplar can use Bonfire to combo. You don't need to normal summon, so if you get hit with a handtrap, you can still combo

The pressure of the deck is huge: recover goods like hacking, monsters jump from the grave + shoot cards as many as the number of people stepped on by Eren's titan, shoot cards, banish, set spell/trap zone boxes to steal monsters to make link material opp monsters onto the field you have it all

Sections covered in this guide:

1/ CORE
2/ Staple
3/ Combo


CORE

 

Snake-Eyes Poplar (x2)

Can you jump automatically when searched to extend combos or combos that don't cost a normal summon so that the handtrap can still be normal summoned?


This card has the ability to search spells/traps. In this deck, you will usually search for Original - a card that jumps more monsters but must send 1 card from the field, and coincidentally, when this card is sent to the grave, it will retrieve 1 FIRE from the grave. up for Original to use

Bonfire (x2)

Searching for a one card combo card, x3 is obvious, but due to being hit, this article only shows x2


Staple

 

Handtrap & Staple

These guys have a one card combo like a hack so you don't care about bringing a lot of handtraps & staples (but peeling all 5 handtraps won't save you).

One for One (x1)

a starter for the deck, sending monsters to the grave is sometimes profitable for you because you can easily jump back from the grave or monsters go to the grave to trigger effects. Level 1 of the deck is all gigachad one card combos (especially Ash) . and Poplar )


Combo

 

Snake-Eye Ash and Legendary Fire King Ponix (All Cumbo)
